In [9]:
gold_price.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan, inplace=True)

# Perform the ADF test
result = adfuller(gold_price['Gold Price'])
print('ADF Statistic:', result[0])
print('p-value:', result[1])
print('Critical Values:')
for key, value in result[4].items():
    print(f'\t{key}: {value}')

if result[1] <= 0.05:
    print("The time series is stationary.")
else:
    print("The time series is non-stationary.")

Check For Normality (Jarque-Bera & Q-Q Plot)¶
In [10]:
def check_normality(data):
    jb_stat, jb_p = jarque_bera(gold_price['Gold Price'])
    print(f"Jarque-Bera Test: {jb_stat}, P-value: {jb_p}")
    if jb_p < 0.05:
        print("❌ Data is NOT normally distributed (reject H0)")
    else:
        print("✅ Data is normally distributed (fail to reject H0)")

    # Plot Q-Q Plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    probplot(data, dist="norm", plot=plt)
    plt.title("Q-Q Plot")
    plt.show()

check_normality(gold_price['Gold Price'])

Jarque-Bera Test: 460.73653744911826, P-value: 8.960496763810149e-101
❌ Data is NOT normally distributed (reject H0)

LSTM for Gold Price¶
In [15]:
def create_sequences(data, seq_length):
    xs = []
    ys = []
    for i in range(len(data) - seq_length - 1):
        x = data[i:(i + seq_length)]
        y = data[i + seq_length]
        xs.append(x)
        ys.append(y)
    return np.array(xs), np.array(ys)

def calculate_aic(y_true, y_pred, num_params):
    """Calculate AIC using Gaussian likelihood approximation."""
    n = len(y_true)
    mse = mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred)
    log_likelihood = - (n / 2) * (np.log(2 * np.pi) + 1 + np.log(mse))
    aic = 2 * num_params - 2 * log_likelihood
    return aic
In [16]:
scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(0,1))
train_data_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(train_data['Gold Price'].values.reshape(-1, 1))

seq_length = 10
X_train_lstm, y_train_lstm = create_sequences(train_data_scaled, seq_length)

X_train_lstm = np.reshape(X_train_lstm, (X_train_lstm.shape[0], X_train_lstm.shape[1], 1))

model_lstm = Sequential()
model_lstm.add(LSTM(units=50, return_sequences=True, input_shape=(X_train_lstm.shape[1], 1)))
model_lstm.add(LSTM(units=50))
model_lstm.add(Dense(1))
model_lstm.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')

# Train the model
model_lstm.fit(X_train_lstm, y_train_lstm, epochs=50, batch_size=32)

# Prepare test data
inputs = gold_price['Gold Price'][len(gold_price) - len(test_data) - seq_length:].values
inputs = inputs.reshape(-1,1)
inputs = scaler.transform(inputs)

X_test = []
for i in range(seq_length, len(inputs)):
    X_test.append(inputs[i-seq_length:i, 0])
X_test = np.array(X_test)
X_test = np.reshape(X_test, (X_test.shape[0], X_test.shape[1], 1))

# Forecasting
lstm_predictions = model_lstm.predict(X_test)
lstm_predictions = scaler.inverse_transform(lstm_predictions)
plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.plot(train_data.index, train_data['Gold Price'], label='Train', color='blue')
plt.plot(test_data.index, test_data['Gold Price'], label='Actual', color='black')
plt.plot(test_data.index, lstm_predictions, label='LSTM Forecast', color='purple', linestyle='dashed')
plt.legend()
plt.title("Gold Price Forecast using LSTM")
plt.show()

Phrophet with Gold Price¶
In [24]:
prophet_df = gold_price.reset_index()
prophet_df = prophet_df.rename(columns={'date': 'ds', 'Gold Price': 'y'})

train_prophet = prophet_df[:int(0.8 * len(prophet_df))]
test_prophet = prophet_df[int(0.8 * len(prophet_df)):]

model = Prophet()
model.fit(train_prophet)
future = model.make_future_dataframe(periods=len(test_prophet), freq='D')
forecast = model.predict(future)

train_fitted_values = model.predict(train_prophet[['ds']])['yhat']

residuals = train_prophet['y'] - train_fitted_values

variance = residuals.var()

#AIC
log_likelihood = -0.5 * len(train_prophet) * (np.log(2 * np.pi * variance) + 1)
n_params = len(model.params['k'])
aic = -2 * log_likelihood + 2 * n_params
print("AIC (Approximation): ", aic)

#RMSE
y_true = test_prophet['y']
y_pred = forecast['yhat'][-len(test_prophet):]
rmse = math.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))
print(f"RMSE: {rmse}")

#Plot predictions
plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.plot(train_prophet['ds'], train_prophet['y'], label='Train', color='blue')
plt.plot(test_prophet['ds'], test_prophet['y'], label='Actual', color='black')
plt.plot(test_prophet['ds'], y_pred, label='Prophet Forecast', color='red', linestyle='dashed')
plt.legend()
plt.title("Gold Price Forecast using Prophet")
plt.show()

Phophet with Log Gold Price¶

prophet_df = gold_price.reset_index()
prophet_df = prophet_df.rename(columns={'date': 'ds', 'log_gold_price': 'y'})

train_prophet = prophet_df[:int(0.8 * len(prophet_df))]
test_prophet = prophet_df[int(0.8 * len(prophet_df)):]

model = Prophet()
model.fit(train_prophet)

future = model.make_future_dataframe(periods=len(test_prophet), freq='D')

forecast = model.predict(future)

train_fitted_values = model.predict(train_prophet[['ds']])['yhat']

residuals = train_prophet['y'] - train_fitted_values
variance = residuals.var()

#AIC
log_likelihood = -0.5 * len(train_prophet) * (np.log(2 * np.pi * variance) + 1)
n_params = len(model.params['k'])
aic = -2 * log_likelihood + 2 * n_params
print("AIC (Approximation): ", aic)


# RMSE
y_true = test_prophet['y']
y_pred = forecast['yhat'][-len(test_prophet):]
rmse = math.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))
print(f"RMSE: {rmse}")

#Plot predictions
plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.plot(train_prophet['ds'], train_prophet['y'], label='Train', color='blue')
plt.plot(test_prophet['ds'], test_prophet['y'], label='Actual', color='black')
plt.plot(test_prophet['ds'], y_pred, label='Prophet Forecast', color='red', linestyle='dashed')
plt.legend()
plt.title("Log Gold Price Forecast using Prophet")
plt.show()
